Cell["\<\
getitpInfo requires an itp file that has been imported as a table from the \
input file section. 
The itp file must have the following sections: [atoms], [constraints], \
[virtualsites3], [bonds], [angles], [dihedrals]. In that order. 
The function parses the itp file to extract information from each section. \
Returns a list of lists of the following:
getitpInfo[[1]] monomer atom definitions
getitpInfo[[2]] monomer constraint definitions
getitpInfo[[3]] monomer virtual site definitions
getitpInfo[[4]] monomer bond definitions
getitpInfo[[5]] monomer angles definitions
getitpInfo[[6]] monomer dihedral definitions\
\>", "CodeText",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.88323009380107*^9, 3.883230099818365*^9}, {
   3.883230143885825*^9, 3.883230401748928*^9}, {3.8832319649731817`*^9, 
   3.883232032414851*^9}, 3.883232953061839*^9, {3.883235844199977*^9, 
   3.883235857530685*^9}, {3.883235906872696*^9, 3.883235960894466*^9}, {
   3.883236044705669*^9, 3.883236159824305*^9}, {3.883747202610264*^9, 
